    "body": "You should be able to set the width of the notebook div by adding custom\nCSS code to $HOME/.ipython/profile_default/static/custom.css. But the width\nis set using CSS media queries so you will probably have to play with those\nas well.\n\nOn Tue, May 27, 2014 at 10:03 AM, bluefir notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> I haven't looked at it for more that half a year and the problem is still\n> there with IPython 2.1.0. Is there a simple configuration change that can\n> solve it? If there is, I would REALLY appreciate if someone pointed it out.\n> For now, I am sticking with version 0.13.\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/4240#issuecomment-44304392\n> .\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\n@ellisonbg on Twitter and GitHub\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
